<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE56FF826BDCD1D8FED5F03D" blockId="16.[151,1436,152,1144]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Herb 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826B92D1D8FEB6F3E5" box="[217,350,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="m" value="0.425" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.35">0.35–0.5 m</quantity>
tall. Rhizomes partly above ground and supported by “stilt” roots, branched to 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE56FF826E49D1D8FA73F3E5" box="[1282,1435,152,178]" form="clusters" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="form">form clusters</taxonomicName>
of 2–8 shoots, each shoot bearing 1–3, irregularly arranged basal leaves. Ultimate basal leaf with sheath 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826E2AD1FEFF54F3A8" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="11.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="9.0">9–14 cm</quantity>
long, papyraceous, glabrous throughout, not auriculate; petiole 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF8268A9D1A5FB8EF3A8" box="[994,1126,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.25" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="9.25" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–15 cm</quantity>
long, laterally flattened, glabrous; pulvinus 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826A31D04CFE17F271" box="[378,511,268,294]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 cm</quantity>
long, laterally flattened, hirtellous adaxially, without annulus; blade narrowly ovate, subcoriaceous, markedly scalloped, base obtuse to truncate, apex caudate, centric, 12–17 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826E59D072FA70F21B" box="[1298,1432,306,332]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="4.7" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="5.6" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="4.7">4.7–6.5 cm</quantity>
, length from base to broadest part 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF82697AD019FD4DF224" box="[561,677,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="4.2" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.4">3.4–5 cm</quantity>
, adaxial surface not papillose, dark green, hirtellous to hirsute throughout, abaxial surface not papillose, greyish green, glabrous. Synflorescence 1-nodate with 2–3 florescences, node with a well-developed leaf, sheath 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF82685BD0E6FC7BF297" box="[784,915,422,448]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.55" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="6.55" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="4.8">4.8–8.3 cm</quantity>
long, petiole 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826F7ED0E6FB50F297" box="[1077,1208,422,448]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="3.35" valueMax="5.2" valueMin="1.5">1.5–5.2 cm</quantity>
long, blade 7–13 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826BDCD08DFEF5F2B0" box="[151,285,461,487]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="4.6" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="4.4">4.4–4.8 cm</quantity>
, peduncle 2.5–5.2(–8.5) cm long, glabrous. Main florescence 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF8268A6D08DFB80F2B0" box="[1005,1128,461,487]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.65" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="7.65" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="4.3">4.3–11 cm</quantity>
long with 3–15 distichous to somewhat unilaterally arranged bracts, first internode 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826867D0B4FC70F159" box="[812,920,500,526]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="1.2" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.0">1–1.4 cm</quantity>
long, peduncle 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826F18D0B4FB3EF159" box="[1107,1238,500,526]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="2.8">2.8–4.2 cm</quantity>
long; lowermost bract 2.3–2.5 × ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826A24D35AFE2AF163" box="[367,450,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="0.6">0.6 cm</quantity>
, pale green, chartaceous, glabrous; first prophyll 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826F49D35AFB68F163" box="[1026,1152,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous. Flowers 4–7 per bract, pale yellowish green to ± hyaline, except for the white outer staminode; pedicel 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826FA8D301FAB1F10C" box="[1251,1369,577,603]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1 mm</quantity>
long; ovary 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826BA8D328FEB5F1D5" box="[227,349,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous; sepals 5.5–6 × ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF8269B7D328FCADF1D5" box="[764,837,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
; corolla tube 19–21 × ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826F32D328FB29F1D5" box="[1145,1217,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, outside glabrous, inside sparsely hirtellous in mouth, lobes 3–4 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF8269A5D3CEFC86F1FF" box="[750,878,654,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
; outer staminode ca 5 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826FEAD3CEFAE2F1FF" box="[1185,1290,654,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
, spathulate, emarginate; stamen 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826ADFD3F5FDFAF198" box="[404,530,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–3 mm</quantity>
long, theca ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF82699FD3F5FCF3F198" box="[724,795,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long; callose staminode 2–2.5 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826F8BD3F5FAAAF198" box="[1216,1346,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
, fleshy throughout, emarginate, with a shelf-shaped callus at ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF82686ED39CFC8FF1A1" box="[805,871,732,758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
from apex; cucullate staminode 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826FAFD39CFAB2F1A1" box="[1252,1370,732,758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–3 mm</quantity>
long, lateral appendage ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826AC6D242FE0EF04B" box="[397,486,770,796]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long; style ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF8269DAD242FD3CF04B" box="[657,724,770,796]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long (untripped), or 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826882D242FBA8F04B" box="[969,1088,770,796]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
long (tripped). Capsule ca 14 × ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826B9BD269FEC5F014" box="[208,301,809,835]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
; seed 12–13.5 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826ABFD269FD87F014" box="[500,623,809,835]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
, brownish, narrowly pyramidal; aril ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826F74D269FB71F014" box="[1087,1177,809,835]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
long, whitish, tubular without lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6B8652FEE56FF826B8DD236FB2FF0E0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE56FF826B8DD236FB2FF0E0" blockId="16.[151,1436,152,1144]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE56FF826B8DD236FE13F0C7" bold="true" box="[198,507,886,912]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="61198806EE56FF826866D236FCB7F0C7" box="[813,863,886,912]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality, where the vegetation was destroyed in late 1986 due to cattle-breeding. It was a primary, lowland terra firme rain forest on latosol.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6B8652FEE56FF826B8DD283FED4F72F" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE56FF826B8DD283FC13F77C" blockId="16.[151,1436,152,1144]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE56FF826B8DD283FEA2F08A" bold="true" box="[198,330,963,989]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE56FF826A24D284FDBCF08A" box="[367,596,964,989]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE56FF826A24D284FDBCF08A" box="[367,596,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Monotagma humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE56FF8269B9D284FC53F08A" box="[754,955,964,989]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="smaragdinum">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE56FF8269B9D284FC53F08A" box="[754,955,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. smaragdinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE56FF8268BED284FB4DF08A" box="[1013,1189,964,989]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flavicomum">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE56FF8268BED284FB4DF08A" box="[1013,1189,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. flavicomum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with which it shares spathulate outer staminodes, but differs by a lower stature, a shorter synflorescence peduncle (2.5–5.2 vs. 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826E3AD2AAFF0BF77C" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="6.4" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="37.5" valueMax="64.0" valueMin="11.0">11– 64 cm</quantity>
), and smaller leaf blades (12–17 × 4.7–6.5 vs. 23–38 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE56FF826825D551FC06F77C" box="[878,1006,1041,1067]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.85" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="cm" value="10.25" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="8.5">8.5–12 cm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
